sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: COMT
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: sarah hollingshead
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
COMT coding sequence
Encodes caffeic acid-O-methyl transferase (methylates -OH on C4 of the aromatic ring) from Medicago sativa (alfalfa), synthesised by Geneart
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Used cDNA as coding gene in Alfalfa genome contains introns.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Alfalfa cDNA
Genes and Enzymes Involved in Caffeic Acid Biosynthesis in the Actinomycete Saccharothrix esanaensis, Berner M, et al, Journal of Bacteriology 188(7): 2666, (2006)
Gowri G, et al, Molecular cloning and expression of alfalfa S-adenosyl-L-methionine: caffeic acid 3-0-methyltransferase, a key enzyme of lignin biosynthesis, Plant Physiology 97(1):7 (1991)
Downregulation of Caffeic Acid 3-O-Methyltransferase and Caffeoyl CoA 3-O-Methyltransferase in Transgenic Alfalfa Impacts on Lignin Structure and Implications for the Biosynthesis of G and S Lignin, Guo D, et al, Plant Cell. January; 13(1): 73 (2001)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1660003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dai Yuanyi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part can express d-limonene synthase with a constitutive promoter J23100, can it can catalyze GPPs into d-limonenen. We use this part to produce d-limonene which is said can attract nematode and some other pests well.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We searched the cDNA sequence in NCBI, and optimized the sequence for E. coli. Meanwhile, we inserted a Xho I restriction site between RBS and d-limonene synthase coding sequence, so that we can change promoter easily.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from Citrus unshiu CitMTSE1 d-limonene synthase.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J45298
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andr?? Green II
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is an intermediate to the protein generator BBa_45300.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BAMT
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: SAM:benzoic acid carboxyl methyltransferase; converts benzoic acid to methyl benzoate (floral odor)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andr?? Green II
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: BAMT catalyzes the transfer of a methyl group from SAM (S-adenosyl methyltransferase) to benzoic acid, creating methyl benzoate. Methyl benzoate produces a "pleasant" smell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Genbank accession number(s): AF198492
This part is from A. majus.

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: A -> G to eliminate SpeI site

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J45098
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Boyuan Zhu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is an intermediate with BSMT hooked up to a terminator. It can be hooked up to a variety of RBS and promoters. This is an early step in creating a "wintergreen generating machine".
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We made (cut) a B0015 backbone for this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from the previous biobrick parts J45004 and B0015.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ATF1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: alcohol acetyltransferase I; converts isoamyl alcohol to isoamyl acetate (banana odor)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andr?? Green II
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the ATF sequence (BBa_45J006) with a single point mutation at base pair 1176 (T -> C).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It has a single point mutation at base pair 1176 (T -> C).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BSMT1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: SAM:benzoic acid/salicylic acid carboxyl methyltransferase I; converts salicylic acid to methyl sali
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Boyuan Zhu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Codes for BSMT enzyme to convert Benzoic acid/salicylic acid to methyl benzoate and methyl salicylate. This part is phBSMT1 from Petunia x hybrida.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Species: Petunia x hybrida from Genbank; (also available: A. thaliana and N. suaveolens)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pchBA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: isochorismate pyruvate-lyase and isochorismate synthase (pchBA); converts chorismate to salicylate
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: MIT IGEM 2006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pchBA codes for proteins used to generate salicylic acid. It doesn't make a fusion protein, even though the coding regions overlap; the RBS for pchA is located at the end of the coding region of pchB.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: pchBA is found in pseudomonas. The plasmid was kindly sent to the MIT iGEM team by Dr. Cornelia Riemmann from the Universite de Lausanne.
